,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تُقَرِّظُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تُقَرِّظْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يُقَرِّظ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تُقَرِّظ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يُقَرِّظانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يُقَرِّظا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تُقَرِّظانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تُقَرِّظا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يُقَرِّظُونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يُقَرِّظُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يُقَرِّظْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نُقَرِّظ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أُقَرِّظ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"قَرَّظْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"قَرَّظْتُ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"}],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35539"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B8%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Acacia spp. or Vachellia spp., especially Vachellia nilotica and Acacia etbaica syn. Vachellia etbaica, and especially its leaves or pods","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tan or dye with قَرَظ (qaraẓ)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pluck the leaves or pods قَرَظ (qaraẓ)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to praise, to eulogize, to commend a living person"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of قَرَظَ (qaraẓa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-West Semitic, cognate to Aramaic קרטא / ܩܷܪܱܛܳܐ (qerraṭṭā, “acacia; carob”), and Ancient Greek κεράτιον (kerátion, “carob tree”), matched to the Semitic. This tree is important for tanning and dying, hence the meaning of “to eulogize”.\nAccording to Löw the Syriac word is from Arabic and the Arabic from Greek, but a borrowing of ظ (ẓ) is hard (save from South Semitic). and the Greek gives regularly already existing قِيرَاط (qīrāṭ).\nDictionnaire du faisceau dialectal arabe andalou considers a borrowing from Egyptian ꜣqrw (“a tree the fruits of which are used officinally”) with an added second element, compare نَبَق (nabaq) where the same seems to have happened."},"ipa":["/qa.raðˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35539","headword_ar":"قَرَظٌ","root":"qrZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to some, (Msb,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaves of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salam","text_ar":"سَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mimosa flava"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Lth, S, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which they tan;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, Mgh;) but this assertion is [said to be] inaccurate; for the leaves are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaT","text_ar":"خَبَط"},{"kind":"text","text":", and camels are fed with them, and they are not used for tanning: some say, that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this also is inaccurate; for one says, “ I plucked, or gathered,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraZ","text_ar":"قَرَظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; ” and trees are not plucked, or gathered: (Msb:) AHn [contradicts this, however, for he applies this word to a kind of tree, and] says, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best of things with which hides are tanned in the land of the Arabs; and these are tanned with its leaves and its fruit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the pods of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanoT","text_ar":"سَنْط"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraZ","text_ar":"قَرَظ"},{"kind":"text","text":", are used for tanning;] and in one place he says, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large kind of trees, having thick stems"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swq","text_ar":"سوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awok","text_ar":"شَوْك"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thorns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the walnut-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Mgh, evidently from the same source, “ or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large kind of trees, having thick thorns"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wok","text_ar":"شوْك"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the walnut-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leaves of which are smaller than those of the apple-tree, and it has grains which are put into balances"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for weights, like as are those of the carob-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it grows in the low plains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of tree, whereof the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanoT","text_ar":"سَنْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mimosa Nilotica, also called acacia Nilotica,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is a species:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"snT","text_ar":"سنط"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [or,] correctly speaking, it is [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seed with its pericarp, of that tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well-known grain, which comes forth in envelopes, like lentils, from the trees called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or, [to speak more precisely,] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanoT","text_ar":"سَنْط"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whence is expressed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqaAqiyaA","text_ar":"اَقَاقِيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acacia,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"succus acaciæ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSaArapu AlqaraZi","text_ar":"عُصَارَةُ القَرَظِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and when inspissated,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~u","text_ar":"رُبُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaraZi","text_ar":"القَرَظِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and has an acrid property; the best thereof is that which is sweet in odour, heavy, hard, and green; and it strengthens relaxed members, when cooked in water, and poured upon them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Jezleh, TA:) [the last application is that which commonly obtains in the present day: see also 'Abd-el-Lateef, pp. 48-52 of the Arabic text, and De Sacy's translation and notes:] the n. un. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraZapN","text_ar":"قَرَظَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHn, Mgh, Msb:) and the dim. of this is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurayoZapN","text_ar":"قُرَيْظَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AHn, Msb.) Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bilaAdu AlqaraZi","text_ar":"بِلَادُ القَرَظِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"El-Yemen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraZ","text_ar":"قَرَظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"grows there [most plentifully]. (S.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SamoEN","text_ar":"صَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","Lth","S","Mgh","K","TA","AHn"]}]}}